WEBVTT

00:02.680 --> 00:04.078
NARRATOR:
Previously on Revolution:

00:04.240 --> 00:08.154
This is Miles Matheson.
Commanding general of the Monroe Militia.

00:08.360 --> 00:11.318
Second only to Sebastian Monroe himself.

00:11.480 --> 00:15.713
We have light. Power. It's time to let
everyone know it, starting with the rebels.

00:15.880 --> 00:18.599
And once that irritation is done,
it's on to Georgia.

00:18.760 --> 00:21.400
MILES: You wanna take down Monroe,
you gotta hit hard.

00:21.560 --> 00:23.949
I'm gonna help you. I'm with the rebels now.

00:24.120 --> 00:27.715
There's still no word from Neville.
Whatever happened, he's failed.

00:27.960 --> 00:30.076
<i>- I'll</i> make the pickup.
CHARLIE: That's Randall Flynn.

00:31.640 --> 00:33.551
RACHEL:
The man was selling Randall a bomb.

00:33.760 --> 00:35.717
- Nuclear?
- How we supposed to fight that?

00:35.880 --> 00:37.757
RACHEL: Charlie, I have to leave.
- Why?

00:37.920 --> 00:40.560
There's this place. It's called the Tower.

00:40.720 --> 00:43.030
I'm gonna turn the power back on
for everybody.

00:43.200 --> 00:46.431
Wait. Isn't there at least
a little chance that I'll see you again?

00:47.040 --> 00:48.713
RACHEL:
Charlie, I'm not coming back.

00:54.400 --> 00:56.869
Honestly, general,
we're still piecing it together...

00:57.040 --> 01:00.829
...but it seems like Major Neville
and his wife fled the city last night.

01:03.040 --> 01:04.235
Why would he do that?

01:04.760 --> 01:06.114
We received some intel.

01:06.600 --> 01:08.910
A few of our spies have
spotted someone that we think...

01:09.480 --> 01:11.869
...may be Major Neville's son, Jason.

01:16.400 --> 01:19.677
- His son?
BURKE: Yes, sir.

01:22.280 --> 01:23.793
Sit.

01:25.320 --> 01:28.517
- His son's dead.
- According to all reports...

01:28.680 --> 01:30.876
...he's with the rebels now.

01:34.720 --> 01:38.554
Well, that means Major Neville
has been lying to me for a while now.

01:40.880 --> 01:43.554
I wonder what else
he's been lying to me about.

01:44.800 --> 01:47.314
Clearly, I've been too kind.

01:49.480 --> 01:51.949
Too trusting, right?

01:57.160 --> 01:59.879
So Major Neville, he never...

02:01.760 --> 02:03.194
...told you about any of this?

02:03.360 --> 02:05.351
No. No, sir. Never.

02:05.680 --> 02:10.197
It's just that you were his most trusted aide.

02:10.400 --> 02:11.799
He trained you, right?

02:12.160 --> 02:13.958
That doesn't mean I was every privy to any--

02:14.120 --> 02:15.269
No.

02:19.400 --> 02:20.470
[SCOFFS]

02:20.640 --> 02:23.519
I used to hear you two just whispering.

02:24.080 --> 02:27.118
Whispering like, uh, housewives.

02:32.360 --> 02:35.318
How do I know I can trust you, captain?

02:38.000 --> 02:40.514
How do I know that you
won't betray me too?

02:40.720 --> 02:42.916
Major Neville was a traitor.

02:43.080 --> 02:44.957
I'm loyal to you.

02:50.840 --> 02:52.911
I'm sure that's true.

03:23.800 --> 03:25.199
[HORSE NEIGHS]

03:28.920 --> 03:30.194
[GRUNTING]

03:31.480 --> 03:32.629
Come on down. I got you.

03:34.280 --> 03:36.749
Medic! Need a medic.

03:38.640 --> 03:40.995
Relax, you'll be okay. You'll be okay.

04:04.320 --> 04:07.312
MILES:
Four of our spies died getting that here.

04:10.840 --> 04:13.070
- Miles, what do we do?
- What is it?

04:13.240 --> 04:15.709
Monroe sent the nuke to Atlanta.

04:17.839 --> 04:21.151
<i>A three-man strike team smuggled it
across the border at Clarksville.</i>

04:21.360 --> 04:23.476
<i>CHARLIE: When?
MILES: <i>A day ago, maybe two.</i></i>

04:23.640 --> 04:25.711
<i>CHARLIE:
You think Monroe's crazy enough to use it?</i>

04:25.880 --> 04:27.279
M I <i>LES:
If Georgia doesn't surrender?</i>

04:28.720 --> 04:30.233
Yeah, I do.

04:31.880 --> 04:35.430
If we could find it in time, do you think--?
Could you disarm it?

04:36.200 --> 04:37.634
I don't know.

04:39.400 --> 04:40.435
I'll give it a shot.

04:42.360 --> 04:44.795
Your confidence is overwhelming.

04:47.720 --> 04:51.350
You're in too.
Your mom told me to take care of you.

04:51.560 --> 04:54.757
So I figured I'd drag you
in front of a nuclear weapon.

04:55.800 --> 04:58.519
Pack your crap. We're going to Georgia.

05:06.080 --> 05:09.311
So this woman we're looking for--

05:09.480 --> 05:11.198
Dr. Warren.

05:11.360 --> 05:12.873
She can get us into the Tower?

05:13.080 --> 05:14.514
She knows the place better than me.

05:14.680 --> 05:15.715
[SCOFFS]

05:15.880 --> 05:19.157
Better than anyone. We need her.

05:35.120 --> 05:36.155
All clear.

05:48.040 --> 05:49.553
What?

05:50.520 --> 05:53.194
I've never left the Monroe Republic.

05:54.400 --> 05:57.313
My God, you're a hick. Let's go.

05:59.120 --> 06:00.713
Come on.

06:19.160 --> 06:20.753
[WHISTLE TOOTING]

06:28.640 --> 06:31.758
Steam engines. And that's just for starters.

06:32.920 --> 06:35.480
Georgia Federation? Whole different world.

06:35.640 --> 06:38.871
- What do you mean?
- Well, they're filthy rich, for one thing.

06:39.080 --> 06:41.469
They got warm weather, lots of crops.

06:42.120 --> 06:44.714
Heard they even started trading with Europe.

06:46.640 --> 06:48.551
Mint juleps and plantations.

06:49.160 --> 06:51.390
Wait till you see Atlanta. It's beautiful.

06:51.600 --> 06:53.750
Not like back home.
Nobody's covered in crap.

06:53.920 --> 06:57.117
It's got a pretty serious gate, Miles.
How we gonna get through?

06:57.960 --> 07:00.076
Well, we can't.

07:00.320 --> 07:02.118
Three soldiers can.

07:02.280 --> 07:05.272
Just gotta look the part. Come on.

07:20.200 --> 07:21.235
MILES:
Okay.

07:21.680 --> 07:23.398
Knock on the door.

07:23.560 --> 07:24.595
Bat your eyelashes.

07:25.600 --> 07:28.433
When soldier boy answers, cut his throat.

08:01.880 --> 08:03.553
[COUGHS]

08:08.480 --> 08:10.391
[FLIES BUZZING]

08:11.120 --> 08:13.031
No sign of struggle.

08:14.320 --> 08:15.674
Perfect head shot.

08:16.120 --> 08:18.111
Monroe's guys must have done this.

08:21.560 --> 08:22.994
They had the same idea we did.

08:24.080 --> 08:27.198
- Cleared out the spare uniforms.
MILES: Then we'll take these uniforms.

08:28.440 --> 08:30.238
Weapons too.

08:45.120 --> 08:46.190
Miles.

08:50.040 --> 08:51.599
I've seen this knife before.

08:52.920 --> 08:53.955
Whose is it?

08:56.320 --> 08:57.879
Mine.

08:59.880 --> 09:01.632
Alec.

09:02.040 --> 09:03.678
He was here.

09:03.840 --> 09:04.910
He did this.

09:05.600 --> 09:07.318
You don't know that.

09:07.760 --> 09:09.080
Same route I would've taken.

09:09.240 --> 09:12.471
That's the move I would've made. It's him.

09:18.800 --> 09:19.835
CHARLIE:
Miles, wait.

09:20.000 --> 09:21.877
- Give him a minute.
- What's going on?

09:23.680 --> 09:24.829
Who's Alec?

09:35.120 --> 09:36.997
<i>MAN:
Remember the first time we met?</i>

09:38.160 --> 09:39.673
Right outside this bar.

09:40.720 --> 09:44.270
Heh. Hey, did you ever think
that kid would make captain?

09:45.400 --> 09:48.358
No, that kid was an idiot.

09:51.000 --> 09:52.354
But...

09:53.640 --> 09:55.517
...gotta say...

09:56.640 --> 09:59.314
...grew into a pretty fine soldier.

10:01.760 --> 10:03.671
It's because I learned from one.

10:14.680 --> 10:16.910
I ever tell you where this knife came from?

10:17.560 --> 10:18.595
No.

10:20.120 --> 10:24.717
My grandfather. Carved the handle himself.

10:25.360 --> 10:26.680
Took it with him to Korea.

10:27.840 --> 10:32.516
When he made it back in one piece,
that made the knife a good-luck charm.

10:33.040 --> 10:34.553
So...

10:35.920 --> 10:38.514
...when my dad shipped out for Vietnam...

10:39.440 --> 10:40.669
...he took it with him.

10:41.480 --> 10:43.756
He made it back home too.

10:44.320 --> 10:47.358
Which made the damn thing miracle-lucky.

10:53.880 --> 10:55.359
Here.

10:57.960 --> 11:00.520
Make sure you always come back alive.

11:03.160 --> 11:04.878
Miles, I can't take this.

11:07.640 --> 11:09.233
.1111

11:10.040 --> 11:11.997
I don't want this.

11:14.920 --> 11:16.433
MILES:
One day...

11:17.680 --> 11:19.637
...maybe your son will.

11:42.120 --> 11:45.158
Oh, great, this isn't super creepy at all.

11:45.320 --> 11:46.833
Your friend lives out here?

11:47.000 --> 11:50.516
Jane can be odd.

11:50.680 --> 11:54.958
So when we find her, try not to set her off,
or make eye contact.

11:56.240 --> 11:57.719
Okay.

11:58.560 --> 11:59.595
MAN:
You folks lost?

12:02.920 --> 12:04.069
Just passing through.

12:08.360 --> 12:12.069
- You know, there's a toll on this road.
- Well, whatever you want.

12:15.960 --> 12:17.553
That's mighty kind of you.

12:17.720 --> 12:19.836
[RACHEL & AARON GRUNT]

12:20.040 --> 12:21.838
- Get your hands off me.
- Not just yet.

12:22.760 --> 12:24.956
Come on, sweetheart.
We're gonna have a good time.

12:25.120 --> 12:27.111
[COUGHING]

12:28.360 --> 12:31.557
- What's the matter with you?
- I don't know.

12:32.040 --> 12:33.553
- I'm burning up.
- What the hell?

12:34.720 --> 12:35.915
[WHEEZING]

12:42.120 --> 12:43.633
[GROANING]

12:52.160 --> 12:54.231
[SCREAMING]

13:00.440 --> 13:02.431
[BOTH PANTING]

13:23.600 --> 13:25.238
Jane.

13:30.040 --> 13:31.155
Rachel.

13:35.240 --> 13:37.277
What are you doing out here?

13:37.480 --> 13:38.675
I came to see you.

13:38.840 --> 13:41.229
Really? Why's that?

13:41.400 --> 13:46.156
Um, hi, sorry, are we just not going to talk
about the magically charred bodies, or...?

13:47.000 --> 13:49.719
- Who's this?
- A friend. He knows.

13:52.880 --> 13:56.236
It's not magic. But it might as well be.

13:59.200 --> 14:00.793
Must be what God feels like.

14:05.040 --> 14:08.032
Come back to the house.
We've got sandwiches.

14:09.120 --> 14:10.633
[AARON PANTS]

14:10.800 --> 14:14.430
[WHISPERS]
I am not hungry anymore.

14:19.040 --> 14:23.830
MAN 1: --that you have no weapons
of any kind in your possession.

14:38.120 --> 14:42.830
Okay, we search here. Alec's gonna spill
as much innocent blood as possible.

14:43.000 --> 14:44.149
How do you know?

14:45.840 --> 14:47.797
Because that's how I taught him.

14:50.400 --> 14:52.198
MAN 2:
I'll take three.

14:52.680 --> 14:55.479
- Flashlights?
- One of those pendants powers the nuke.

14:55.640 --> 14:57.836
Which means it'll power anything
in its range.

15:18.520 --> 15:20.079
[BEEPS]

15:44.880 --> 15:45.950
[BOTH GRUNT]

15:54.640 --> 15:55.675
Hey, Miles.

15:57.760 --> 15:59.114
Alec.

16:04.920 --> 16:06.558
How long you been back in Philly?

16:08.200 --> 16:09.429
About a year.

16:13.640 --> 16:16.712
You know, Monroe
said you might come looking for it.

16:17.120 --> 16:18.235
Did you get my message?

16:26.360 --> 16:31.355
Well, turns out it wasn't so lucky
for me after all.

16:31.520 --> 16:33.033
Alec.

16:34.040 --> 16:36.270
- What I did to you--
- Hey.

16:36.640 --> 16:39.792
It was for the good of the republic, right?

16:44.560 --> 16:45.959
[DRAWS SWORD]

16:46.760 --> 16:48.398
[BOTH GRUNTING]

17:20.040 --> 17:21.758
Come on, old man.

17:26.800 --> 17:27.949
[GROANS]

17:37.520 --> 17:39.511
Miles? Miles.

17:41.400 --> 17:44.279
Go. Go. He's got the nuke.

17:49.080 --> 17:50.150
<i>Out of my Way'-!</i>

17:50.320 --> 17:51.355
[MAN 3 GRUNTS]

17:55.760 --> 17:57.512
- Move!
WOMAN 1: Hey!

18:01.960 --> 18:02.995
WOMAN 2:
Excuse me.

18:03.160 --> 18:04.719
[WOMAN 3 SCREAMS]

18:05.600 --> 18:06.635
Get out!

18:09.040 --> 18:10.314
[WOMAN 4 SCREAMS]

18:29.560 --> 18:31.198
Go that way.

18:43.520 --> 18:44.919
[WOMAN 5 SCREAMS]

18:45.080 --> 18:46.275
[GRUNTS]

18:47.600 --> 18:48.999
Hey!

18:50.160 --> 18:53.198
Alec, come on.
You think I care if you kill some cop?

18:53.840 --> 18:56.116
See, that's the thing, Miles. I didn't kill him.

18:57.160 --> 18:58.833
- You did.
MILES: Alec--!

18:59.000 --> 19:00.035
[GUNSHOT]

19:07.760 --> 19:08.909
You, don't move!

19:35.640 --> 19:37.358
What now?

19:37.520 --> 19:40.876
We'll never find Alec or that bomb
without Miles.

19:42.000 --> 19:44.230
How are we gonna get him out?

19:45.480 --> 19:47.073
Let's take a look.

19:54.440 --> 19:56.511
Beth, I've got a surprise for you.

20:03.160 --> 20:06.949
Rachel Matheson, oh, my God.

20:07.600 --> 20:09.238
Oh.

20:11.360 --> 20:12.680
[BETH CHUCKLES]

20:12.840 --> 20:13.875
You look wonderful.

20:14.040 --> 20:15.474
[CHUCKLES]

20:15.640 --> 20:17.472
What are you doing out here?

20:18.960 --> 20:21.634
Uh, traveling through, uh...

20:21.800 --> 20:23.029
...on our way to Colorado.

20:23.240 --> 20:26.676
Well, that's quite a trip. What's in Colorado?

20:27.520 --> 20:28.555
Unfinished business.

20:29.160 --> 20:33.518
Uh, Beth, why don't you, um,
give this chubby gentleman some lunch?

20:35.680 --> 20:37.478
- Thanks.
BETH: Mm-hm.

20:42.680 --> 20:44.478
Rachel.

20:44.680 --> 20:46.512
Some fresh air?

20:48.920 --> 20:53.835
JANE: Why would you go to the Tower?
- You know why, Jane.

20:54.840 --> 20:58.231
We need to turn the power back on.
For everyone.

20:58.480 --> 21:01.757
- You're going to destroy the nanites?
- And I need your help to do it.

21:01.920 --> 21:03.911
Even though they're keeping your son alive?

21:12.280 --> 21:14.032
What happened?

21:14.320 --> 21:16.834
Something not even your little machines
could fix.

21:20.360 --> 21:22.112
Randall...

21:22.480 --> 21:24.232
-...is in the Tower.
- Oh.

21:24.400 --> 21:26.516
God knows what he can do.

21:26.720 --> 21:29.360
Oh, please.
What could Randall possibly do to me?

21:29.520 --> 21:33.195
This is bigger
than what happens to you and me.

21:37.880 --> 21:41.191
The person I love most on this planet...

21:41.400 --> 21:44.995
...is in her 16th year of Stage 4 cancer.
She's a miracle.

21:45.160 --> 21:48.790
Those nanites are inside of her,
eating away at her tumors.

21:48.960 --> 21:51.793
Just like they were inside of Danny.

21:54.600 --> 21:56.796
They do more than keep the power off.

21:59.920 --> 22:01.433
I know.

22:03.520 --> 22:05.636
I know what I'm asking.

22:07.440 --> 22:08.874
I don't think you do.

22:09.040 --> 22:11.395
Either that, or you don't care.

22:11.760 --> 22:15.913
You short-circuit the nanites, all of them,
everywhere, and Beth dies.

22:16.320 --> 22:19.472
You flip the switch at the Tower,
you flip the switch on her too.

22:19.640 --> 22:21.119
- Jane--
- Rachel.

22:21.280 --> 22:24.557
I strongly suggest that you drop this.

22:46.560 --> 22:48.915
Gotta admit, you're a pretty good shot.

22:49.080 --> 22:50.115
[BOTH GRUNTING]

22:50.280 --> 22:52.032
So, what are you, huh?

22:53.240 --> 22:55.436
Miles' new sidekick?

22:55.640 --> 22:57.119
See, I feel for you.

22:57.280 --> 23:00.033
- Hell, I'm here to warn you. About Miles.
- Really?

23:00.200 --> 23:02.396
Sure. I mean, you're the new me, aren't you?

23:03.000 --> 23:05.435
Huh? Aren't you?

23:11.360 --> 23:13.670
I was right where you're standing.

23:14.440 --> 23:16.750
My guess is you got no one else, huh?

23:16.920 --> 23:18.069
Orphan, probably.

23:20.280 --> 23:21.554
And then there's Miles.

23:22.480 --> 23:26.599
With the swagger and the sword tricks.
And you wanna learn from him.

23:26.840 --> 23:29.753
And eventually, you think
you mean something to him, hmm?

23:30.400 --> 23:31.470
But you don't.

23:31.720 --> 23:34.280
He could give a crap about you.

23:34.440 --> 23:36.431
You're a means to an end.

23:37.000 --> 23:40.789
- You're meat for the grinder.
- He wouldn't do that to me.

23:41.640 --> 23:43.631
What makes you so special, princess?

23:44.480 --> 23:46.278
He's my uncle, for one.

23:49.480 --> 23:52.916
Really. You're Rachel Matheson's daughter?

23:53.600 --> 23:55.034
You know what Miles did to her?

23:56.600 --> 23:58.591
You don't think he'd hurt you? Huh?

23:59.640 --> 24:01.677
Ask him what he did to your mom sometime.

24:01.880 --> 24:03.359
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

24:06.760 --> 24:08.433
[CHARLIE YELLS]

24:13.200 --> 24:14.759
MAN 1 :
What is it?

24:17.520 --> 24:21.229
MAN 2: Oh, no! We've gotta get out of here!
Go, just leave it!

24:24.560 --> 24:26.198
[CROWD SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

24:39.120 --> 24:41.111
[MILES PANTING]

24:46.960 --> 24:48.359
FOSTER:
Miles Matheson.

24:49.560 --> 24:51.551
Madam President.

24:53.600 --> 24:57.559
May I just say, that was a crapload of stairs.

24:59.440 --> 25:01.272
FOSTER:
Charming as ever.

25:01.960 --> 25:04.952
I suppose you're gonna tell me
you didn't kill that policeman.

25:05.960 --> 25:07.439
Nope.

25:08.280 --> 25:12.160
But the man who did, he's your problem.

25:12.360 --> 25:14.715
Oh, he's a hell of a problem.

25:16.720 --> 25:19.439
A little mash note from Sebastian.

25:20.360 --> 25:23.079
"Dear citizens, our fight is not with you.

25:23.240 --> 25:25.834
It is with your leaders who insist upon war."

25:26.560 --> 25:29.916
If the Georgia Federation does not offer
an unconditional surrender...

25:30.080 --> 25:33.755
...by midnight tonight,
he's going to detonate a nuke.

25:35.000 --> 25:36.877
You must have heard he got power.

25:38.200 --> 25:39.270
Hmm.

25:44.040 --> 25:47.351
A nuclear bomb.
And he's deranged enough to use it.

25:47.560 --> 25:48.959
Kelly.

25:56.280 --> 26:00.319
He wants your real estate. You know that.

26:01.880 --> 26:04.633
Let me out of here. I can help.

26:04.800 --> 26:06.154
[SCOFFS]

26:08.200 --> 26:10.157
I should trust you?

26:11.720 --> 26:13.631
Miles...

26:14.520 --> 26:16.955
...I should slit you wide open.

26:19.160 --> 26:20.958
You've killed how many of my troops?

26:22.280 --> 26:24.430
- That was a long time ago.
FOSTER: Oh.

26:25.440 --> 26:28.114
And what about what you did to me...

26:28.280 --> 26:29.953
...personally?

26:34.120 --> 26:35.519
Kelly.

26:38.920 --> 26:41.434
The guy who brought this bomb here...

26:42.840 --> 26:44.513
...I trained him.

26:45.760 --> 26:47.671
I can stop him.

26:49.600 --> 26:51.716
And hell, if I'm wrong...

26:52.040 --> 26:54.873
...we're all in the same dust cloud anyway.

26:58.920 --> 27:01.116
NORA:
You saw Alec?

27:01.480 --> 27:03.710
What happened? What did he say?

27:03.880 --> 27:06.838
He didn't say anything, all right?
We don't have a lot of time.

27:07.040 --> 27:08.314
How are we gonna get Miles?

27:08.560 --> 27:11.074
Maybe we don't.
Maybe we just gotta find that bomb.

27:11.240 --> 27:13.754
Well, thank you, Nora,
I appreciate the loyalty.

27:13.920 --> 27:17.197
Come on.
I've been looking all over for you guys.

27:17.440 --> 27:19.033
[CROWD SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

27:23.240 --> 27:24.958
MAN:
Let's go!

27:28.880 --> 27:31.349
NORA:
Miles, you think the bomb's here?

27:31.520 --> 27:33.636
Alec's gonna detonate where the people are.

27:33.800 --> 27:36.030
They're not in the city anymore, they're here.

27:37.120 --> 27:38.315
It's gonna be here.

27:45.520 --> 27:46.590
MILES:
Alec.

27:50.720 --> 27:52.313
Welcome home.

28:02.320 --> 28:04.038
How'd the job go?

28:06.280 --> 28:07.350
Smooth.

28:10.200 --> 28:12.794
No, Alec, it didn't.

28:15.200 --> 28:16.952
General Blanchard survived.

28:17.560 --> 28:20.678
- No. No, no, no. I--
- You winged him.

28:24.840 --> 28:26.751
And he made the shooter.

28:34.640 --> 28:37.200
We can't afford to go to war with Texas.

28:38.160 --> 28:39.912
You know that.

28:43.040 --> 28:45.031
I've gotta give them something.

28:51.160 --> 28:52.514
- Miles--
- He saw your face.

28:52.680 --> 28:54.671
You know what they'll do to me.

28:56.280 --> 28:58.635
- You know, Miles.
- We can't go to war.

28:58.840 --> 29:00.433
We won't win.

29:00.640 --> 29:01.835
Miles.

29:02.600 --> 29:04.511
This is the job.

29:06.560 --> 29:07.755
[SCOFFS]

29:07.920 --> 29:09.240
The job?

29:11.560 --> 29:15.235
After everything, this is about the job?

29:15.440 --> 29:17.431
Miles, okay. Miles-- Hey! Get off me.

29:17.600 --> 29:19.238
Miles, if I mean anything to you...

29:19.440 --> 29:20.714
...please don't do this.

29:21.160 --> 29:23.595
I can fix this. If you just give me the time.

29:23.760 --> 29:26.320
Just a little bit more time.
We can fix this. Miles.

29:28.000 --> 29:29.718
Miles?

29:31.600 --> 29:32.920
[DOOR OPENS]

29:34.120 --> 29:35.440
[DOOR CLOSES]

29:38.520 --> 29:39.999
[CROWD SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

29:40.160 --> 29:41.275
MAN 1:
Hurry, come on!

29:44.160 --> 29:45.912
- Come on, get up, get up.
WOMAN 1: Thank you.

29:46.080 --> 29:47.798
You okay? Go, 90, 90-

29:49.640 --> 29:52.598
MAN 2: Let's go, hurry!
Many yards outside the city!

29:52.760 --> 29:54.319
This way!

29:54.520 --> 29:57.160
MAN 3: Hurry, come on!
WOMAN 2: Come on, this way!

30:21.640 --> 30:23.199
JANE:
Rachel.

30:25.320 --> 30:27.914
Rachel, what do you think you're doing?

30:30.880 --> 30:32.871
We have killed...

30:33.480 --> 30:35.630
...too many people.

30:37.920 --> 30:39.877
We have to stop this thing.

30:41.440 --> 30:43.750
This thing kept your son alive.

30:44.400 --> 30:45.515
And only now...

30:46.600 --> 30:49.558
...now you're asking me
to sacrifice my family?

30:49.720 --> 30:52.394
My son is not alive.

30:53.400 --> 30:58.474
I did awful things for him, and...

31:00.000 --> 31:01.752
...he's dead.

31:04.160 --> 31:06.879
None of it mattered.

31:07.560 --> 31:10.871
And you're saying to save him,
you wouldn't have done it all again?

31:21.680 --> 31:22.954
No.

31:24.720 --> 31:26.154
I wouldn't.

31:26.360 --> 31:27.953
I would...

31:29.440 --> 31:33.593
I would hate myself. No.

31:35.840 --> 31:37.478
- I don't believe you.
- Jane.

31:37.640 --> 31:38.789
I am so disappointed in you.

31:39.000 --> 31:40.115
[DEVICE POWERING ON]

31:40.280 --> 31:41.714
- Don't.
BETH: Jane?

31:42.800 --> 31:44.552
[DEVICE POWERS DOWN]

31:46.360 --> 31:48.033
- Is this true?
- Beth, please listen.

31:48.200 --> 31:52.114
This whole time, you've known
how to turn the power back on?

31:53.800 --> 31:55.598
If I do it...

31:56.880 --> 31:58.632
...you will die.

32:02.520 --> 32:04.397
- Give her what she wants.
- Beth, no--

32:04.560 --> 32:07.200
If you don't help her, I swear...

32:07.400 --> 32:09.516
...I will slash my wrists.

32:09.680 --> 32:12.877
And then you won't have anything
to worry about.

32:16.160 --> 32:19.039
Give her what she wants.

32:46.800 --> 32:49.553
JANE: This will tell you
everything you need to know.

32:51.720 --> 32:53.393
Get out.

32:53.640 --> 32:55.551
And don't come back.

33:55.400 --> 33:57.550
So they let you go, huh?

34:00.360 --> 34:02.271
You really gonna blow yourself up?

34:06.240 --> 34:07.469
All those people out there?

34:07.640 --> 34:09.391
[ALEC GRUNTING]

34:17.480 --> 34:18.594
ALEC:
That's the job, Miles.

34:21.360 --> 34:23.158
Job comes first.

34:25.440 --> 34:27.431
That's what you taught me.

34:34.880 --> 34:35.995
Yeah, I was wrong.

34:36.159 --> 34:41.188
See, now, that doesn't sound
like the General Matheson I know.

34:46.320 --> 34:49.710
I'm trying really hard...

34:49.960 --> 34:51.234
...not to be him.

34:53.280 --> 34:54.759
No.

34:57.080 --> 34:58.115
You were right.

35:00.480 --> 35:02.710
See, it took me a while...

35:03.720 --> 35:05.631
...to figure it out...

35:06.640 --> 35:08.119
...but you had to give me up.

35:11.840 --> 35:13.558
Or it would've been war.

35:15.480 --> 35:16.550
No.

35:17.680 --> 35:19.830
I should've been looking out for you.

35:20.040 --> 35:22.509
- Should have protected you.
- No.

35:23.240 --> 35:24.310
Don't tell me that.

35:27.680 --> 35:29.830
You sent me to Texas.

35:31.280 --> 35:32.793
Miles...

35:33.600 --> 35:35.273
...all those years.

35:38.320 --> 35:40.072
And I did it.

35:40.520 --> 35:42.989
Oh, I did it, I did it for the republic.

35:44.960 --> 35:46.678
I did it for you.

35:49.440 --> 35:51.590
And then I come back...

35:52.560 --> 35:53.994
...and you're gone?

35:55.520 --> 35:57.477
Like it was all some mistake?

36:01.200 --> 36:03.430
Like it was for nothing?

36:04.480 --> 36:06.756
MAN [OVER <i>RADIO]:
Strike team, this is Philadelphia.</i>

36:06.920 --> 36:09.196
<i>Your mission is a go. Detonate.</i>

36:09.960 --> 36:12.156
<i>Repeat, detonate.</i>

36:16.680 --> 36:19.274
Strike team, do you copy?

36:19.440 --> 36:20.714
[BOTH GRUNTING]

36:20.880 --> 36:22.279
MAN: <i>Your mission is</i> a <i>go.</i>

36:22.440 --> 36:25.273
Strike team, come in.
There's no response, sir.

36:26.920 --> 36:29.753
Alec, this is General Monroe. Do you copy?

36:29.920 --> 36:33.276
Your mission is a go. Alec, do you copy?

36:34.200 --> 36:35.429
Alec, do you copy?

36:37.200 --> 36:39.316
<i>Your mission is a go. Do you copy?</i>

36:47.200 --> 36:49.555
<i>Do you copy, Alec?</i>

36:58.600 --> 37:00.159
<i>Alec, do you copy?</i>

37:01.160 --> 37:03.356
Come on, Alec, don't do it. Don't do it!

37:03.560 --> 37:04.789
You did this.

37:07.280 --> 37:08.918
[KNIFE PIERCES FLESH]

37:10.160 --> 37:12.197
MONROE:
Do you <i>copy?</i>

37:17.000 --> 37:18.479
[GASPS]

37:48.000 --> 37:51.118
MONROE: <i>Alec, your mission is</i> a <i>go. Do you copy?</i>

37:52.080 --> 37:54.310
Do you copy, Alec?

38:27.040 --> 38:28.997
I need to ask you something about Alec.

38:29.640 --> 38:31.358
Not now.

38:34.800 --> 38:37.314
He said you did something...

38:37.880 --> 38:39.439
...to my mom.

38:40.520 --> 38:43.911
- What's he talking about?
- It doesn't matter.

38:44.640 --> 38:47.280
Miles, I just wanna know the truth.

38:56.000 --> 38:58.719
The truth is, people count on me...

39:00.440 --> 39:02.158
...and they get hurt.

39:03.240 --> 39:04.469
Wanna know why?

39:06.560 --> 39:08.597
Because I hurt them.

39:11.200 --> 39:14.238
And I don't even think twice about it.

39:18.440 --> 39:20.795
That's who I am, Charlie.

39:22.480 --> 39:26.269
- Now get the hell away from me.
- President Foster wants to see you.

39:36.320 --> 39:37.799
<i>FOSTER:
Where's the rest of it?</i>

39:38.200 --> 39:41.477
The radioactive material, Miles, where is it?

39:41.640 --> 39:42.675
MILES:
Why?

39:42.840 --> 39:45.275
So you can build a nuke of your own?

39:59.840 --> 40:02.150
Monroe knows
he can't take me on the ground.

40:02.320 --> 40:04.755
My men outnumber his two to one.

40:06.200 --> 40:10.558
I'm supposed to run and hide
because he has power?

40:11.600 --> 40:13.955
Well, sweetheart, I have money.

40:15.000 --> 40:17.116
I got tall ships in Savannah.

40:17.280 --> 40:18.953
Aid from England.

40:19.120 --> 40:22.511
His third-world ass is gonna mess with me?

40:28.080 --> 40:29.559
Well...

40:33.560 --> 40:36.359
...if he wants all-out war, he's got it.

40:39.280 --> 40:40.429
Have fun with that.

40:42.160 --> 40:43.719
If you'll excuse me.

40:43.880 --> 40:45.871
FOSTER:
Hold on. Miles.

40:50.040 --> 40:53.032
My men will attack his southern border.

40:53.360 --> 40:57.035
I want you and your rebels
to hit Monroe from the inside.

40:57.200 --> 40:59.396
Open up a second front.

41:02.600 --> 41:03.999
Kelly...

41:05.440 --> 41:07.954
...I don't have that kind of manpower...

41:08.200 --> 41:10.157
...on my best day.

41:19.880 --> 41:22.349
FOSTER:
A couple hundred men. A thousand guns.

41:22.520 --> 41:24.431
All yours.

41:25.280 --> 41:26.998
What do you say, Miles?

41:27.160 --> 41:29.470
Ready to be a general again?

42:09.800 --> 42:11.837
[English - US - SDH]
